{{About|the Buddha's disciple|the supplementary Mon language chronicle|Gavampati (chronicle)}}

'''''Gavāṃpati''''' is a disciple of the Buddha, one of the first ten to be ordained and to have known the state of [[Arhat]]. In Southeastern Buddhism, Gavāṃpati has become a preeminent character. In [[Thailand]], [[Laos]], [[Cambodia]], and the [[Shan states]], the Mon cult of Gavampati has survived.<ref>{{Cite book|title = Encyclopedia of Buddhism|last = Buswell|first = Robert E.|publisher = Macmillan Reference USA|year = 2004|isbn = 978-0028657189|location = New York|pages = 301–302}}</ref>

